			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-8">
					<img src="_ext/img/foto_5.jpg" alt="Agriturismo Firenze"	class="img-responsive img_large_home">
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-4 col-xs-12">
					<div class="module-subtitle font-serif text-offset">
						Podere Moricci is a country house completely immersed in the picturesque <strong>Tuscan landscape</strong> around <strong>Montaione</strong>. 
						It lies on a hill in the heart of the splendid <strong>Chianti</strong> countryside with a panoramic view of great beauty and fascination.  
						This typical Tuscan farmhouse was recently renovated with all modern comforts and preserving its 
						original structure and ancient style. It is divided into 8 independent <strong>apartments</strong> and <strong>2 houses</strong>, 
						the Scuderia and the Terrazza, developed from a separate barn.  
					
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="row">
					<div class="col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3">
						<div class="large-text align-center">
							<a href="#features" class="section-scroll"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i></a>

							<div class="clear_20"></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
												<div class="col-md-6">
					<div class="module-subtitle font-serif large-text text-cinzel">
						Located 50 km southeast of <strong>Florence</strong>, it is a great base from which to explore the cultural and art attractions of <strong>Tuscany</strong> and its main cities as <strong>Siena</strong>, <strong>Arezzo</strong>, <strong>Pisa</strong> and the <strong>Maremma</strong> coast.<br /><br /> The centre of <strong>Certaldo, Volterra and San Gimignano</strong>, the famous medieval village with towers, are just few km from <strong>Podere Moricci</strong> and at 8 Km is set the beautiful and renowned golf course to 36 holes of Castelfalfi.<br />
						<br /> <img src="_ext/img/foto_12.jpg" alt="Agriturismo Firenze" class="img-responsive"><br />
					</div>
				</div>
				
				<div class="col-md-6">
					<div class="module-subtitle font-serif large-text text-cinzel">
						The property dates back to the 18th century and lies in a natural environment along a stretch of the <strong>Via Francigena</strong>, which passes through the village of <strong>Montaione</strong>. It is surrounded by the vineyards for the finest <strong>Chianti</strong>, by olive groves and woods that makes the farmhouse the ideal place to spend a relaxing holiday.
In the local territory, you can go on excursions along signposted hiking trails taking you to ancient Etruscan and medieval ruins and crossing some of the most beautiful landscapes of the surroundings.<br />
						
						<br /> <img src="_ext/img/foto_11.jpg" alt="Agriturismo Firenze" class="img-responsive"><br />
					</div>
				</div>
							</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</div>		
		<div class="row">
	<div class="col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3">
		<div class="large-text align-center">
			<i style="color:#9d1a1a;" class="fa fa-angle-down"></i>
			<div class="clear_20"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
	

